
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gnome-language-selector` baraye taeen zaban-e default (pishfarz) dar system-e amale GNOME estefade mishavad. Ba in dastoor mitoonid zaban-e system, format-haye tarikh va adad, va keyboard layout ra tagheer dahid. 🌐

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gnome-language-selector` --> 🚀 Baz kardan barname-ye entekhab zaban ba GUI (Graphical User Interface).
    🔹 `gnome-language-selector --help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-language-selector

    🔹 Barname-ye entekhab zaban ra baz mikonad ke shoma mitoonid zaban-e system ra az aanjaa tagheer dahid.

    $ gnome-language-selector --help

    🔹 Rahnamaye dastoor ra dar terminal namayesh midahad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-language-selector

    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, yek panjare baz mishavad ke shoma mitoonid zaban-e system ra be zaban-e farsi ya har zaban-e digar tagheer dahid. ⌨️

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gnome-language-selector` command is used to set the default language in the GNOME operating system.  With this command, you can change the system language, date and number formats, and keyboard layout. 🌐

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gnome-language-selector` --> 🚀 Opens the language selection program with a GUI (Graphical User Interface).
    🔹 `gnome-language-selector --help` --> ❓ Displays the command help and options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-language-selector

    🔹 Opens the language selection program, from where you can change the system language.

    $ gnome-language-selector --help

    🔹 Displays the command help in the terminal.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-language-selector

    🔹 By running this command, a window opens where you can change the system language to Persian or any other language. ⌨️

